Angola’s 2048 issue dropped 10.95 cents in the dollar to 61.25 cents, having nearly halved in price from their mid-February peak when they traded at nearly 112 cents, Tradeweb data showed. Bonds issued by Africa’s top oil exporter Nigeria maturing in 2049 tumbled 8.6 cents to 76.6 cents, a sharp decline from the 117 cents in February. Fellow crude producer Gabon also felt the pressure, with its 2024 dollar bonds slipping nearly 8 cents to 81.05 cents. --Reuters--